Third-party notices: QR Code generator library (MIT)
================================================================================

The ki-qr component vendors a minimal adaptation of the reference QR Code
generator by Project Nayuki so that encoding is local, auditable and adds no
runtime npm dependency (constitution Art. X):

  - packages/elements/src/components/ki-qr/qr-encoder.ts
    QR Code generator library (TypeScript) — Project Nayuki
    https://www.nayuki.io/page/qr-code-generator-library
    https://github.com/nayuki/QR-Code-generator
    Version pinned: release v1.8.0
    Reference file: typescript-javascript/qrcodegen.ts
    SHA-256 (reference file at v1.8.0):
    c4749095a91bf9696e3a303998b9905e467094f53041e64393e65e6d887737fd
    Copyright (c) Project Nayuki
    License: MIT

  Kimen adaptations (the file header carries the same record): TypeScript
  namespace converted to an ES module with a single `encodeQr` entry point;
  only the byte mode at the fixed MEDIUM error-correction level is kept
  (numeric/alphanumeric/kanji/ECI segments, ECC boosting and the mask
  override are removed); capacity overflow returns null instead of throwing;
  tables trimmed to the MEDIUM rows; grids flattened to Uint8Array; strict
  TypeScript hardening. The algorithm — function patterns, Reed-Solomon ECC
  over GF(2^8/0x11D), block interleaving, mask selection and penalty
  scoring, format/version bits — is Nayuki's, per ISO/IEC 18004.

